==English==
===Etymology===
From {{It.}}, {{Sp.}} or mediaeval {{L.}}, from {{Arab.}} {{ARchar|[[جبر|الجبر]]}} (al-jabr) "reunion", "resetting of broken parts", used in the title of [[w:Al-Khwarizmi|al-Khwarizmi]]’s influential work {{ARchar|علم الجبر والمقابلة}} (ilm al-jabr wa’l-muqābala), "the science of restoration and equating like with like"
[[Category:Arabic derivations]]

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
{{en-noun|s|-}}

# {{math}} {{uncountable}} A system for computation using letters or other symbols to represent numbers, with rules for manipulating these symbols.
# {{math}} A structure consisting of a set of [[element]]s together with one or more [[operations]] and rules specifying what expressions are equivalent.
# {{math}} {{uncountable}} The study of algebras.

